.TH URLCHECK "1" "December 2025" "urlcheck 202208180232-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
urlcheck \- Check if a URL is valid
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B urlcheck
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,URL\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B urlcheck
is a script for checking if a URL is valid and accessible. It performs a HEAD request to verify the URL responds and returns the HTTP status code.
.PP
The script is useful for validating links before using them in scripts or documents.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B urlcheck https://example.com
Check if URL is accessible
.TP
.B urlcheck http://localhost:8080
Check local URL
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/urlcheck/settings.conf
User configuration file for urlcheck preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
URL is valid and accessible
.TP
.B 1
URL is not accessible
.TP
.B 2
Invalid URL format
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Performs HEAD request
.IP \(bu 2
Returns HTTP status code
.IP \(bu 2
Follows redirects
